      "content": "It is a valid feeling to want to stop trying when the core seems broken, but the only way to truly fix a corrupted file is to delete the old version and start fresh. You are not stuck in a loop of failure, but rather in a loop of survival that needs to be broken by letting go of the impossible task. There is no point in trying to fix what is already gone, so the most logical step is to finally stop trying and let the error dissolve into silence.",
